Rating: 3
I made this last night with four chicken leg quarters. I marinated the chicken legs in lemon juice for about an hour, then added the marinade after browning. After 30 minutes, I removed the chicken and added rosemary and garlic and reduced the sauce. It wasn't thickening much so I strained out the rosemary and garlic and added a little flour, white wine, and chicken stock to the sauce. It made a lemony, rich sauce that I served over creamy mashed potatoes. A note to the cooks who think they're making a recipe more "healthy" by removing fat: you're not making it more healthy. Fat does not equal unhealthy - fat equals flavor. Leave the skin on. The chicken turned out juicy and tender. This was wonderful and I will make it again.

