Rating: 4
This dish was so easy, absolutely delicious and super low fat with the modifications that I used. First I used 6 skinless chicken legs (all the fat is in the skin - you won't miss the skin this way I promise!). I marinated them all day in lemon juice, rosemary and a table spoon of dijon mustard. To cook them, I lightly sprayed the pan with olive oil and sauteed the chicken legs with garlic for 5 minutes. They were nicely browned. Then I added a mixture of 1/4 cup of chicken broth, 1/4 cup of white wine, the rest of the marinade and an extra pinch of rosemary. I covered the pan and let it simmer for 30 minutes. It formed the most amazing rich sauce. The chicken was so tender it just fell off the bone. We served this with the Oven Roasted Vegetables with Garlic on this site. I also added potatoes to the vegie dish. The vegies were the perfect compliment to the chicken and sauce. My husband mopped up the rest of the sauce with some bread - he couldn't let it go to waste!

